\subsection{Activity Diagrams}

This section describes the activity diagrams of the Fair and Unbiased Assessment System (FUAS). 
Activity diagrams represent the dynamic behavior of the system by illustrating the sequence of 
actions performed by different system actors. The activities are categorized according to the 
three primary user roles: Student, Teacher, and Administrator.

% ==================================================
\subsubsection{Student Activity Diagram}

The Student Activity Diagram illustrates the workflow followed by a student while interacting 
with the system from login to logout.

\textbf{Key Activities}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Login to the system using institutional credentials.
    \item Access the student dashboard after successful authentication.
    \item Check the availability of quizzes, assignments, or assessments.
    \item Upload handwritten answer sheets in image or PDF format.
    \item Wait for the automated assessment evaluation process.
    \item View detailed assessment reports generated by the system.
    \item Analyze class performance graphs if marks visibility is enabled.
    \item Logout from the system after completing activities.
\end{itemize}

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.85\textwidth]{Act st.png}
\caption{Student Activity Diagram of the Fair and Unbiased Assessment System}
\label{fig:student-activity}
\end{figure}

% ==================================================
\subsubsection{Teacher Activity Diagram}

The Teacher Activity Diagram represents the sequence of tasks performed by a teacher to create, 
manage, and evaluate assessments.

\textbf{Key Activities}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Login to the system using teacher credentials.
    \item Access the teacher dashboard to manage assigned courses.
    \item Select a course and create a new assessment.
    \item Define submission portal start and end timings.
    \item Upload answer keys for automated evaluation.
    \item Enable or disable student submission options.
    \item Review system-generated class performance reports.
    \item Control the visibility of marks for students.
    \item Logout from the system after task completion.
\end{itemize}

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{Act fac.png}
